            .card
              a.card-header(data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq2") I absolutely loved this book, and don't often read science fiction so I'm not sure what book to search for. Does anyone have a suggestion for a book to read that gives you similar feelings as "The Martian"?
              #faq2.collapse(role="tabpanel" data-parent="#accordion")
                .card-body
                  p I highly recommend Seveneves, by Neal Stephenson, which deals with spaceflight and has long passages explaining a lot of the science. It's got space, realistic science, humour, and nerdy characters, so I think you'll love it.
                  cite Jack Brady
            
            .card
