              #faq3.collapse(role="tabpanel" data-parent="#accordion")
                .card-body
                  p No, probably half of the book covers Mark's challenges. At some point, the book starts shifting back and forth between Mark and other people. But if you don't like the "how does he solve these problems" part, you won't like the book.
                  cite Laurie
            
            .card
              a.card-header(data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq4") I'm curious if NASA would ever send people to Mars? If they did, what would we be hoping to learn?
              #faq4.collapse(role="tabpanel" data-parent="#accordion")
                .card-body
                  p Mary Roach has a non-fiction book called Packing for Mars and its all about the various space-programs around the world and preparations they are making to eventually send astronauts there - its kinda quirky, but intriguing
                  cite Dee
            
            .card
              a.card-header(data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq5") Can anyone please tell me how much swearing is in here? I'm interested in this book, and would like to read it, but I'm a bit hesitant...
              #faq5.collapse(role="tabpanel" data-parent="#accordion")
                .card-body
                  p A LOT of swearing. Lots of f-bombs thrown around. Usually doesn't get worse than the f-bomb, but lots of other lower kinds of swearing too. But probably worth mentioning that characters rarely ever swear at each other.
                  cite Tushmit
            

